Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}. Cut the courgette into four long strips. Chop each strip into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Heat a #frying pan{} over medium heat and add a splash of @oil{}. When the oil is hot, add your courgette and cook for ~{3%minutes}. Add your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more before adding the @basmati rice{175%g}. Stir to coat your rice in the garlicky oil.

Add the @water{350%ml} to the frying pan along with the @vegetable stock pot{1} and bring to the boil. Stir to make sure your stock pot dissolves. Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium, pop the lid on and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Whilst your rice cooks, get on with the rest of your prep. Place the @salmon fillets{2}(skin-side down) on a #foil lined baking tray{} and sprinkle over half of the @za'atar spice{1.5%tbsp}. Use your hands to make sure the zahtar spice is evenly spread over each salmon fillet. Season each fillet with a pinch of @salt{} and keep to one side. Preheat your #grill{} to its highest setting.

When your rice has been cooking for 10 mins, remove the frying pan from the heat, pop in the @baby spinach{1} and put the lid back on. Leave the frying pan to one side for ~{10%minutes}. The steam in the pan will finish cooking your rice and wilt your spinach.

Zest and juice the @lemon{1/2}. Mix the remaining zahtar spice with a pinch of lemon zest and @oil{1%tbsp} per person. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and stir well.

Put your salmon under your grill and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Tip: The salmon is cooked when the centre is opaque.

Once your salmon is cooked, remove the tray from under your grill and add a dash of lemon juice.

Finish your rice by mixing through the @ground coriander{1.5%tsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Add a dash of lemon juice and a pinch of lemon zest if it needs a bit of zing!

Serve your salmon on top of a bed of your fragrant rice and finish with a drizzle of your zahtar dressing. Enjoy!